text: The Seawolf class of submarines is a class of three nuclear-powered submarines built for the United States Navy in the 1990s. originally, there were going to be 29 submarines; however, due to the expense of the submarines, only three were built.. There are three boats in the class: USS Seawolf, USS Connecticut, and USS Jimmy Carter. All three of them are still in service today. Category:Submarines of the United States Navy
title: Seawolf-class submarine
